Title: Aidex Continuous Glucose Monitoring Transmitter
Description: Transmitter The transmitter in a continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) device is a crucial component that works alongside the sensor to relay glucose data to a smartphone. The transmitter is typically attached to the sensor, and it wirelessly communicates with the sensor to collect glucose readings. The sensor detects glucose levels in the interstitial fluid and converts this into an electrical signal and transfer the data to mobile app.

Title: Aidex Continuous Glucose Monitoring Sensor
Description: Sensor The sensor used in a continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) device is typically a small, disposable electrode or filament that is inserted just under the skin (usually in the abdomen or upper arm). This sensor measures the glucose levels in the interstitial fluid (fluid surrounding the cells) continuously throughout the day and night for 10 days. The sensor works by detecting the glucose in the interstitial fluid and converting this into an electrical signal. This signal is then transmitted
